50|$|Ingeborg {{wanted to}} go back to France but the French refused a visa on her <b>stateless</b> <b>passport.</b> She found a new {{supporter}} and friend, the U.S. Attaché Culturel who invited her to his house in Sao Paulo. Through him and his wife she met the American consul who offered her an emigration visa to New York. In September 1948 she embarked on a Moore McCormack ship sailing to New York.|$|E
