5000|$|Nansen <b>passports,</b> officially <b>stateless</b> persons <b>passports,</b> were internationally {{recognized}} refugee travel documents, first {{issued by the}} League of Nations to stateless refugees. They quickly became known as [...] "Nansen passports" [...] for their promoter, the statesman and polar explorer Fridtjof Nansen.|$|R
